                                <div class="pt-3 mr-2 science--paragraph-section-1">
                                    <p class="paragraph-text--medium-condensed-20">Classic Galactosemia (pronounced ga-lac-toe-SEE-me-ah) is a rare condition where the body has trouble breaking down a sugar called “galactose.”
                                    </p>

                                    <p class="paragraph-text--regular-16"><strong>Galactose</strong> is a type of sugar most commonly found in milk, dairy products, and certain other foods. Lactose, a complex sugar found in milk, dairy products and certain other foods is broken down within the body into equal parts of the simple sugars glucose and galactose. Galactose is also made naturally in the body—this is called “endogenous” galactose.</p>
                                </div>

