                                            <h2 class="text-center">Toxic galactitol</h2>
                                            <img src="./assets/images/science/Legend@2x.png" width="668" />
                                            <div class="flex-wrap" style="padding-top:1rem;padding-left:11rem; padding-right:11rem;">
                                                <p class="paragraph-text--regular-16 text-left">Because people with Galactosemia cannot complete the process of metabolizing Gal-1p, excess galactose backs up and is abnormally converted by an enzyme called <strong>Aldose Reductase</strong> through another pathway that is not usually involved. Then, this enzyme turns galactose into toxic galactitol.</p>
                                            </div>

